wfX25State.name: wfX25State
wfX25State.description: The current state of the entire X.25.

wfX25ServiceTable.name: wfX25ServiceTable
wfX25ServiceTable.description: This table describes the services of a circuit on an X.25 line.

wfX25ServiceEntry.name: wfX25ServiceEntry
wfX25ServiceEntry.description: An entry in the X25 Service table.

wfX25ServiceSlot.name: wfX25ServiceSlot
wfX25ServiceSlot.description: Slot number and part of Instance Id.

wfX25ServiceConnector.name: wfX25ServiceConnector
wfX25ServiceConnector.description: Connector number and instance ID member.

wfX25ServiceLineNumber.name: wfX25ServiceLineNumber
wfX25ServiceLineNumber.description: Instance identifier member. This is the line number assigned to the driver X.25 is running over. No used in 7.60.

wfX25ServiceLLIndex.name: wfX25ServiceLLIndex
wfX25ServiceLLIndex.description: Instance identifier member. This is the lower layer index presented to X25 by the layer immediately below it on the protocol stack. If the lower layer is a driver, the index will be 0. Not used in 7.60.

wfX25ServiceCct.name: wfX25ServiceCct
wfX25ServiceCct.description: Circuit number and instance ID member.

wfX25ServiceIndex.name: wfX25ServiceIndex
wfX25ServiceIndex.description: X.25 service entry record ID for this instance.

wfX25ServiceConnRef.name: wfX25ServiceConnRef
wfX25ServiceConnRef.description: Use of Connection Reference Numbers in Call Request For PDN only, if ON then use wfX25ServiceConnId as starting reference number for PDN.

wfX25ServiceConnId.name: wfX25ServiceConnId
wfX25ServiceConnId.description: Connection Id to be used in a PTOP Call request. For PDN this will be the starting number to be used as Connection Id in PDN.

wfX25ServiceRemoteX121Addr.name: wfX25ServiceRemoteX121Addr
wfX25ServiceRemoteX121Addr.description: Remote X.121 address for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceRemoteIpAddr.name: wfX25ServiceRemoteIpAddr
wfX25ServiceRemoteIpAddr.description: Remote IP address for PDN and DDN only.

wfX25ServiceBCast.name: wfX25ServiceBCast
wfX25ServiceBCast.description: Broadcast recipient status for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceMaxConn.name: wfX25ServiceMaxConn
wfX25ServiceMaxConn.description: Maximum connections per destination for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServicePrecedence.name: wfX25ServicePrecedence
wfX25ServicePrecedence.description: Precedence value for this table entry instance. DDN only.

wfX25ServiceMaxIdle.name: wfX25ServiceMaxIdle
wfX25ServiceMaxIdle.description: Maximum Idle Time in Minutes for this table entry instance. If 0 is entered the connection stays on forever.

wfX25ServiceCallRetry.name: wfX25ServiceCallRetry
wfX25ServiceCallRetry.description: Interval in seconds between Call Request to same the destination. Must be at least 2 times T11/T21 Timer for Packet Level.

wfX25ServiceFlowFacility.name: wfX25ServiceFlowFacility
wfX25ServiceFlowFacility.description: Flow Control negotiation facility parameter for this instance.

wfX25ServiceWinSize.name: wfX25ServiceWinSize
wfX25ServiceWinSize.description: Packet window size parameter for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServicePktSize.name: wfX25ServicePktSize
wfX25ServicePktSize.description: Packet size parameter for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceFastSelRequest.name: wfX25ServiceFastSelRequest
wfX25ServiceFastSelRequest.description: Fast Select Request Facility for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceFastSelAccept.name: wfX25ServiceFastSelAccept
wfX25ServiceFastSelAccept.description: Fast Select Accept Facility for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceRevChRequest.name: wfX25ServiceRevChRequest
wfX25ServiceRevChRequest.description: Reverse Charge Request Facility for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceRevChAccept.name: wfX25ServiceRevChAccept
wfX25ServiceRevChAccept.description: Reverse charge Accept Facility for this table entry instance.

wfX25ServiceCugType.name: wfX25ServiceCugType
wfX25ServiceCugType.description: Closed User Group Facility Type: Normal CUG, Bilateral CUG, or Outgoing Access CUG.

wfX25ServiceUserFacility.name: wfX25ServiceUserFacility
wfX25ServiceUserFacility.description: Additional User Supplied Facilities. Must be in Hexadecimal form.

wfX25ServiceValid.name: wfX25ServiceValid
wfX25ServiceValid.description: Validity of the record - updated by X.25.

wfX25ServiceForceCugZero.name: wfX25ServiceForceCugZero
wfX25ServiceForceCugZero.description: Force Closed User Group of Zero.

wfX25ServiceMUX.name: wfX25ServiceMUX
wfX25ServiceMUX.description: Set to Enabled to perform 1356 Multiplexing of protocols in the same Vc

wfX25ServicePtopCallRequest.name: wfX25ServicePtopCallRequest
wfX25ServicePtopCallRequest.description: Select which side of PTOP circuit initiates the connection. (default = highest X.121 address initiates the call)

wfX25ServiceVcType.name: wfX25ServiceVcType
wfX25ServiceVcType.description: Determines whether this service record represents a Switch Virtual Circuit (SVC) or Permanent Virtual Circuit (PVC). (default = svc)

wfX25ServicePvcLcn.name: wfX25ServicePvcLcn
wfX25ServicePvcLcn.description: PVC Logical Channel Number for this service record

wfX25ServiceMacPoolStart.name: wfX25ServiceMacPoolStart
wfX25ServiceMacPoolStart.description: Starting address of MAC address pool

wfX25ServiceMacPoolSize.name: wfX25ServiceMacPoolSize
wfX25ServiceMacPoolSize.description: The size of MAC address pool

wfX25ServiceWindowTimeout.name: wfX25ServiceWindowTimeout
wfX25ServiceWindowTimeout.description: Window Timeout to detect a dysfunctional VC.

wfX25ServiceVcBurstThroughput.name: wfX25ServiceVcBurstThroughput
wfX25ServiceVcBurstThroughput.description: Maximum number of bits of data allowed to be transmitted for this service record in one second. This value is divided equally amongst the VCs active for this service record at any given point in time. A value of 0 indicates Burst control is not to be applied. The default value is 0.

wfX25ServiceVcBurstQDepth.name: wfX25ServiceVcBurstQDepth
wfX25ServiceVcBurstQDepth.description: Maximum number of buffers that can be held in the Burst Queue while the VC gate pends.

wfX25ServiceVcPriority.name: wfX25ServiceVcPriority
wfX25ServiceVcPriority.description: Priority of the VCs associated with this service record. This value is used to specify whether packets being transmitted for this VC will be given preference over those on another VC or not. In the range for this value, 1..9999, 1 signifies highest priority.

wfX25ServiceVcBurstQClippedPkts.name: wfX25ServiceVcBurstQClippedPkts
wfX25ServiceVcBurstQClippedPkts.description: Total Number of packets dropped for VCs of this service record due to lack of buffers in their respective Burst Queues.

wfX25ServiceVcBurstQPktCnt.name: wfX25ServiceVcBurstQPktCnt
wfX25ServiceVcBurstQPktCnt.description: Total Number of packets stored in the Burst Queues of VCs of this service record between successive attempts to forward to the PLP layer.

wfX25ServiceVcBurstQHighWaterPkts.name: wfX25ServiceVcBurstQHighWaterPkts
wfX25ServiceVcBurstQHighWaterPkts.description: The Highest Water Packet Mark of the Burst Queues of VCs of this service record.

wfX25ServiceVcPktDrops.name: wfX25ServiceVcPktDrops
wfX25ServiceVcPktDrops.description: Total Number of Packets Dropped for VCs of this service record at the VC level.

wfX25ServicePlpPktDrops.name: wfX25ServicePlpPktDrops
wfX25ServicePlpPktDrops.description: Total Number of Packets Dropped by PLP for VCs of this service record.

wfX25ServiceBurstThrPerVc.name: wfX25ServiceBurstThrPerVc
wfX25ServiceBurstThrPerVc.description: Burst Throughput per VC, dynamically computed as Burst Throughput confiogured for the service record divided by number of VCs for the service record in Data Transfer State.

wfX25ServiceBackupRecoveryDelay.name: wfX25ServiceBackupRecoveryDelay
wfX25ServiceBackupRecoveryDelay.description: Delay in reverting back to a restored PDN service

wfX25ServiceSetupTime.name: wfX25ServiceSetupTime
wfX25ServiceSetupTime.description: Total time allowed for setting up a PDN SVC before attempting a backup

wfX25ServiceRetryNumber.name: wfX25ServiceRetryNumber
wfX25ServiceRetryNumber.description: The number of times a PDN SVC setup will be attempted if no response is received from the peer

wfX25BackupInitiation.name: wfX25BackupInitiation
wfX25BackupInitiation.description: Determines whether to initiate PDN backup on failure of any SVC or the last one

wfX25VcTable.name: wfX25VcTable
wfX25VcTable.description: This is a table of Statistic Entries is per Virtual Circuit.

wfX25VcEntry.name: wfX25VcEntry
wfX25VcEntry.description: An entry in the X.25 VC table.

wfX25VcSlotNum.name: wfX25VcSlotNum
wfX25VcSlotNum.description: Instance ID and Slot number this VC is on.

wfX25VcConnector.name: wfX25VcConnector
wfX25VcConnector.description: Instance ID and Connector number this VC is using

wfX25VcLineNumber.name: wfX25VcLineNumber
wfX25VcLineNumber.description: Instance identifier member. This is the line number assigned to the driver X25 is running on top of and this VC is running on. No used in 7.60

wfX25VcLLIndex.name: wfX25VcLLIndex
wfX25VcLLIndex.description: Instance identifier member. This is the lower layer index presented to X25 by the layer immediately below it on the protocol stack. If the lower layer is a driver, the index will be 0. Not used in 7.60.

wfX25VcCct.name: wfX25VcCct
wfX25VcCct.description: Instance ID and CCT supporting these VCs. User determines this CCT via log.

wfX25VcNumber.name: wfX25VcNumber
wfX25VcNumber.description: Instance ID and VC number for this VC. This number corresponds to the LCN.

wfX25VcRrTxs.name: wfX25VcRrTxs
wfX25VcRrTxs.description: Number of Receiver Ready Packets sent.

wfX25VcRnrTxs.name: wfX25VcRnrTxs
wfX25VcRnrTxs.description: Number of Receiver Not Ready Packets sent.

wfX25VcIntBytesTxs.name: wfX25VcIntBytesTxs
wfX25VcIntBytesTxs.description: Number of Interrupt Data Bytes sent.

wfX25VcRrRxs.name: wfX25VcRrRxs
wfX25VcRrRxs.description: Number of Receiver Ready Packets received.

wfX25VcRnrRxs.name: wfX25VcRnrRxs
wfX25VcRnrRxs.description: Number of Receiver Not Ready Packets received.

wfX25VcIntBytesRxs.name: wfX25VcIntBytesRxs
wfX25VcIntBytesRxs.description: Number of Interrupt Data Bytes received.

wfX25VcRemoteX121Addr.name: wfX25VcRemoteX121Addr
wfX25VcRemoteX121Addr.description: Remote DTE Address for this connection

wfX25VcBurstQClippedPkts.name: wfX25VcBurstQClippedPkts
wfX25VcBurstQClippedPkts.description: Number of packets dropped for this VC due to lack of buffers in the Burst Queue. Packets are only dropped when the value of the statistic wfX25VcBurstQPktCnt is equal to wfX25ServiceVcBurstQDepth.

wfX25VcBurstQPktCnt.name: wfX25VcBurstQPktCnt
wfX25VcBurstQPktCnt.description: Number of packets stored for this VC in the Burst Queue between successive attempts to forward to the PLP layer. This statistic is indicative of the transient loading of buffering mechanism between the PLP layer and the upper layers. The maximum value that this statistic can reach is determined by the setting of wfX25ServiceVcMaxBufCnt. When the value of this statistic is equal to wfX25ServiceVcBurstQDepth, all subsequently arriving packets are dropped.

wfX25VcBurstQHighWaterPkts.name: wfX25VcBurstQHighWaterPkts
wfX25VcBurstQHighWaterPkts.description: High Water Packet Mark for the Burst Queue of this VC.

wfX25VcPktsLargerThanBurstThrCnt.name: wfX25VcPktsLargerThanBurstThrCnt
wfX25VcPktsLargerThanBurstThrCnt.description: Total Number of Packets serviced on this VC which are larger than the computed burst throughput per VC. The burst throughput per VC is computed as wfX25ServiceVcBurstThroughput / No. of Active VCs for the service record.

wfX25VcPktDrops.name: wfX25VcPktDrops
wfX25VcPktDrops.description: Total Number of Packets Dropped on this VC. These drops are caused by insufficient resources being available to forward the packets to the PLP layer.

wfX25VcPlpPktDrops.name: wfX25VcPlpPktDrops
wfX25VcPlpPktDrops.description: Total Number of Packets Dropped by PLP on this VC. These drops are due to either the line being disabled or the lack of buffering to store packets for transmission.

wfX25VcMbsOutstanding.name: wfX25VcMbsOutstanding
wfX25VcMbsOutstanding.description: Number of packets sent to the PLP layer from the upper layer that have not yet been added to the local assembly/deassembly queue at the PLP layer. These packets will require additional processing at a later time. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed processing of the maximum allowable number of packets received from the upper layer.

wfX25VcMbsOutstandingPostTx.name: wfX25VcMbsOutstandingPostTx
wfX25VcMbsOutstandingPostTx.description: Number of buffers sent to the PLP layer that have not yet been added to the local asembly/deassembly queue. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed transmission of the maximum allowable number of packets from the local assembly/ deassembly queue to the lower layer.

wfX25VcMaxTx.name: wfX25VcMaxTx
wfX25VcMaxTx.description: Maximum Number of buffers that can be sent from the upper layer to the PLP layer at any one time without overflowing the local assembly/desasembly queue.

wfX25VcMbsQueueCnt.name: wfX25VcMbsQueueCnt
wfX25VcMbsQueueCnt.description: Number of buffers sent to the PLP layer that are currently on the local assembly/deassembly queue at the PLP layer. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed processing of the maximum allowable number of packets received from the upper layer.

wfX25VcMbsQueueCntPostTx.name: wfX25VcMbsQueueCntPostTx
wfX25VcMbsQueueCntPostTx.description: Number of buffers sent to the PLP layer that have not yet been added to the local assembly/deassembly queue. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed transmission of the maximum allowable number of packets from the local assembly/ deassembly queue to the lower layer.

wfX25VcTxQueueCnt.name: wfX25VcTxQueueCnt
wfX25VcTxQueueCnt.description: Number of buffers sent to the PLP layer that are currently on the transmit queue at the PLP layer. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed processing of the maximum allowable number of packets received from upper layer.

wfX25VcTxQueueCntPostTx.name: wfX25VcTxQueueCntPostTx
wfX25VcTxQueueCntPostTx.description: Number of buffers sent to the PLP layer that are currently on thequeue to transmit at the PLP layer. This value is set after the PLP layer has completed transmission of the maximum allowable number of packets from the local assembly/deassembly queue to the lower layer.

wfLapbPktTable.name: wfLapbPktTable
wfLapbPktTable.description: The table of LAPB PKT Level Parameters

wfLapbPktEntry.name: wfLapbPktEntry
wfLapbPktEntry.description: An entry in the LAPB PKT table

wfLapbPktSlotNum.name: wfLapbPktSlotNum
wfLapbPktSlotNum.description: Instance identifier. This is the slot number where this X.25 packet layer is running.

wfLapbPktConnector.name: wfLapbPktConnector
wfLapbPktConnector.description: Instance identifier. This is the Physical connector number for the Physical layer associated with this X25 Packet layer.

wfLapbPktLineNumber.name: wfLapbPktLineNumber
wfLapbPktLineNumber.description: Instance identifier. This is the line number assigned to the LAPB Driver associated with this X25 Packet Layer. Not used in 7.60

wfLapbPktLLIndex.name: wfLapbPktLLIndex
wfLapbPktLLIndex.description: Instance identifier. This is the lower layer index presented to X25 by the layer immediately below it on the protocol stack. If the lower layer is a driver, the index will be 0. Not used in 7.60.

wfLapbPktLapbCct.name: wfLapbPktLapbCct
wfLapbPktLapbCct.description: Circuit number of Lapb (SYNC) driver associated with this X25 Packet Layer

wfLapbPktLinkId.name: wfLapbPktLinkId
wfLapbPktLinkId.description: Access Link identifier - index into line information array.

wfLapbPktLineState.name: wfLapbPktLineState
wfLapbPktLineState.description: Reflects the state of the X.25 packet layer that is associated with this network record. When the state of this parameter is set to Up, the router can transfer data between the line layer and the packet layer. Note that this parameter is used internally; it does NOT reflect the status of the underlying synchronous circuit.

wfLapbPktSeqSize.name: wfLapbPktSeqSize
wfLapbPktSeqSize.description: Sequence numbering scheme for the data packets. Modulo 8 or Modulo 128

wfLapbPktMaxWindow.name: wfLapbPktMaxWindow
wfLapbPktMaxWindow.description: Maximum window size that can be negotiated on a per call basis, if the flow control facility is subscribed too. Extended window size of 127 can be used if wfLapbPktSeqSize is 128. Otherwise the maximum is 7. This attribute is effective only if the attribute wfLapbPktFloCtl is set to 'ON'.

wfLapbPktMaxLength.name: wfLapbPktMaxLength
wfLapbPktMaxLength.description: Maximum packet length that can be negotiated on a per call basis, if the flow control facility is subscribed too. This attribute is effective only if the attribute wfLapbPktFloCtl is set to 'ON'. This attribute should not be greater than the wfSYNCEntry attribute wfSyncMtu.

wfLapbPktMaxThroughput.name: wfLapbPktMaxThroughput
wfLapbPktMaxThroughput.description: Maximum throughput class value that can be negotiated on a per call basis, if the throughput class negotiation facility is subscribed too. For this to be effective the attribute wfLapbPktThroughput must be set to ON.

wfLapbPktFlowCtl.name: wfLapbPktFlowCtl
wfLapbPktFlowCtl.description: Flow control parameter negotiation facility subscription

wfLapbPktUserIdentity.name: wfLapbPktUserIdentity
wfLapbPktUserIdentity.description: Network user identification (NUI) related facility subscription

wfLapbPktInCalls.name: wfLapbPktInCalls
wfLapbPktInCalls.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) incoming calls are permitted

wfLapbPktOutCalls.name: wfLapbPktOutCalls
wfLapbPktOutCalls.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) outgoing calls are permitted

wfLapbPktFastAccept.name: wfLapbPktFastAccept
wfLapbPktFastAccept.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) fast select acceptance facility is subscribed too.

wfLapbPktReverseAccept.name: wfLapbPktReverseAccept
wfLapbPktReverseAccept.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) reverse charge aceptance facility is subscribed to. If this is set this packet layer will simply accept calls with reverse charge facility. But the packet layer (router) will not provide any charging information.

wfLapbPktFastSelect.name: wfLapbPktFastSelect
wfLapbPktFastSelect.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) fast select facility is allowed on a per call basis.

wfLapbPktReverseCharging.name: wfLapbPktReverseCharging
wfLapbPktReverseCharging.description: Specifies whether or not (ON/OFF) reverse charging facility is allowed on a per call basis.

wfLapbPktCugSelection.name: wfLapbPktCugSelection
wfLapbPktCugSelection.description: Format of the Closed User Group (CUG) related facilities supported.

wfLapbPktCugOA.name: wfLapbPktCugOA
wfLapbPktCugOA.description: Specifies whether or not CUG with Outgoing access selection facility is supported.

wfLapbPktCugBilateral.name: wfLapbPktCugBilateral
wfLapbPktCugBilateral.description: Specifies whether or not Bilateral Closed User Group related facility is supported. If this is set, then the wfLapbPktCugSelection should be set to EXTENDED.

wfLapbPktRpoaSelection.name: wfLapbPktRpoaSelection
wfLapbPktRpoaSelection.description: Specifies whether or not RPOA related facility is supported. Outgoing calls will not contain any RPOA facility. But if set this packet layer will simply accept calls with RPOA related facility.

wfLapbPktChargeInform.name: wfLapbPktChargeInform
wfLapbPktChargeInform.description: Specifies whether or not the charging information related facilities are supported. Outgoing calls will not contain the charge information related facility. But if set this packet layer will simply accept calls with the charge information related facility. No charging information will be collected.

wfLapbPktTransitDelay.name: wfLapbPktTransitDelay
wfLapbPktTransitDelay.description: Transit delay indication facility. If set, accept calls with this facility.

wfLapbPktFullAddressing.name: wfLapbPktFullAddressing
wfLapbPktFullAddressing.description: If this attribute is set, the full local X121 address (calling address) is supplied in the outgoing call request and the X.25 network also expected to provide the full called address in the incoming call packet.

wfLapbPktAccFormat.name: wfLapbPktAccFormat
wfLapbPktAccFormat.description: Specifies the format of the call accepted packet.

wfLapbPktRelFormat.name: wfLapbPktRelFormat
wfLapbPktRelFormat.description: Connection release format - format of Clear Requests

wfLapbPktT1.name: wfLapbPktT1
wfLapbPktT1.description: Local confirmation timeouts in seconds. This timer represents the following CCITT timers. If DCE: T10 (restart), T12 (reset), T13 (clear) If DTE: T20 (restart), T22 (reset), T23 (clear)

wfLapbPktT2.name: wfLapbPktT2
wfLapbPktT2.description: Call confirmation time out in seconds. This represent the CCITT T11 timer for the DCE and T21 timer for the DTE.

wfLapbPktT3.name: wfLapbPktT3
wfLapbPktT3.description: Congestion or busy condition watchdog timer in milliseconds. When system resources needed for packet assembly/deassembly depleted, this timer is set to reenter the PLP state machine to retry. User should use extreme caution in manipulating this timer.

wfLapbPktT4.name: wfLapbPktT4
wfLapbPktT4.description: Data packet transmission watchdog timer in milliseconds. This is the delay for acknowledgement. It is used to reenter PLP state machine also. User should use extreme caution in manipulating this timer.

wfLapbPktIwcCnt.name: wfLapbPktIwcCnt
wfLapbPktIwcCnt.description: Number of IWC (Incoming VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktIwcId.name: wfLapbPktIwcId
wfLapbPktIwcId.description: Low LCN ID for IWC (Incoming VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktBwcCnt.name: wfLapbPktBwcCnt
wfLapbPktBwcCnt.description: Number of BWC (Bidirectional VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktBwcId.name: wfLapbPktBwcId
wfLapbPktBwcId.description: Low LCN ID for BWC (Bidirectional VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktOwcCnt.name: wfLapbPktOwcCnt
wfLapbPktOwcCnt.description: Number of OWC (Outgoing VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktOwcId.name: wfLapbPktOwcId
wfLapbPktOwcId.description: Low LCN ID for OWC (Outgoing VC's) defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktDefWindow.name: wfLapbPktDefWindow
wfLapbPktDefWindow.description: Non standard default transmit/receive window size.

wfLapbPktDefLength.name: wfLapbPktDefLength
wfLapbPktDefLength.description: Non standard default transmit/receive packet size. This attribute should not be greater than the wfSyncEntry attribute wfSyncMtu.

wfLapbPktDefClass.name: wfLapbPktDefClass
wfLapbPktDefClass.description: Non standard default transmit/receive throughput class assignment.

wfLapbPktDxe.name: wfLapbPktDxe
wfLapbPktDxe.description: Specify type of local X25 interface and imply subsequent rules of X.25. DXE_X25DTERSTA ->DTE mode with Restart Procedure. DXE_X25DTE ->DTE mode without any restart procedure DXE_X25DCE ->DCE mode with restart procedure DXE_X25DTEDXE ->DTE/DTE environment, unassigned roles.

wfLapbPktConformance.name: wfLapbPktConformance
wfLapbPktConformance.description: CCITT conformance recommendation used on each line.

wfLapbPktStandard.name: wfLapbPktStandard
wfLapbPktStandard.description: Network Standard to be used on each line.

wfLapbPktStatistics.name: wfLapbPktStatistics
wfLapbPktStatistics.description: Gives the user the ability to Turn ON or Shut OFF statistics computation. This can be shut off for better performance on the line. Now it also provides a small packet trace function.

wfLapbPktNetaddrType.name: wfLapbPktNetaddrType
wfLapbPktNetaddrType.description: This defines whether the Network connection is to a DDN network or PDN Network. This is used to decide how the Local X121 Network address is derived. If this attribute is set to DDN the Local X121 address used in the attribute wfLapbPktNetaddr will be derived from the user supplied IP address. Otherwise the X121 address should be supplid by the user.

wfLapbPktDDNIpAddr.name: wfLapbPktDDNIpAddr
wfLapbPktDDNIpAddr.description: If the wfLapbPktNetaddrType is DDNTYPE or DDN_BFE this is the user supplied local IP address. The router will convert this to the corresponding X121 address and the X121 address value will be put in wfLapbPktNetaddr attribute.

wfLapbPktPDNX121Addr.name: wfLapbPktPDNX121Addr
wfLapbPktPDNX121Addr.description: If the wfLapbPktNetaddrType is PDNTYPE this is the user supplied local X.121 address. The router will put this value in wfLapbPktNetaddr attribute.

wfLapbPktTxT5.name: wfLapbPktTxT5
wfLapbPktTxT5.description: Tx window size transmit delay timer

wfLapbPktUseDfltService.name: wfLapbPktUseDfltService
wfLapbPktUseDfltService.description: Indicates whether or not to use the default ddn service.

wfLapbPktPVCCnt.name: wfLapbPktPVCCnt
wfLapbPktPVCCnt.description: Number of PVCs defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktPVCLowLcn.name: wfLapbPktPVCLowLcn
wfLapbPktPVCLowLcn.description: Low LCN ID for PVCs defined on this access link.

wfLapbPktClientTimer.name: wfLapbPktClientTimer
wfLapbPktClientTimer.description: Client application response timeout period in seconds. This timer allows for the extended delays that can occur negotiating with remote clients (e.g., IPEX or QLLC). This timer must be greater than the wfLapbPktT3 period and less than wfLapbPktT2.

wfLapbPktPduSize.name: wfLapbPktPduSize
wfLapbPktPduSize.description: The X.25 PDU Size for this logical channel. This PDU size represents the M_BUF_SIZE used for X.25 Fragmentation and Reassembly in the packet layer. This is the largest message size X.25 will handle from a client on a given Logical Channel. Changing this attribute enables X.25 to handle client messages up to 4096 bytes in length

wfLapbPktTxMbsQueueThreshold.name: wfLapbPktTxMbsQueueThreshold
wfLapbPktTxMbsQueueThreshold.description: The maximum number of packets that TX mbs queue can hold. If X.25 receives more packets and TX mbs queue count reaches this maximum, it will open up another SVC connection. The default is zero and the maximum queue count is equal to wfLapbPktDefWindow + 1, which is three.

wfX25QllcAddrMapOptions.name: wfX25QllcAddrMapOptions
wfX25QllcAddrMapOptions.description: This object is a bitmask, setting individual bit postions enable the option. Values may be added together to enable multiple options. Hex Dec Value Value Options --------------------------------------------------------- 0x0001 1 Do not wait for Adjacent DTE/DCE to send an QXID before forwarding an QXID to it. 0x0002 2 Enable when SDLC endstations are connecting to QLLC hosts that do not support receipt of XID polls and do not retransmit XIDs. 0x0004 4 wfX25QllcAddrMapPartnerMac field contains wildcard characters.

wfX25QllcAddrMapTrace.name: wfX25QllcAddrMapTrace
wfX25QllcAddrMapTrace.description: This object is a bitmask, setting individual bit postions enable logging of internal QLLC messages and events. Values may be added together to enable multiple message groups. Hex Dec Value Value Message/Event --------------------------------------------------------- 0x0001 1 Enable QLLC logging. 0x0002 2 Data frames/packets. 0x0004 4 Flow Control messages. 0x0008 8 Client registration messages. 0x0010 16 X.25 session establishment messages. 0x0020 32 Test frames/packets. 0x0040 64 XID frames/packes. 0x0080 128 Set Mode frames/packets. 0x0100 256 Disconnect frames/packets. 0x0200 512 Configuration changes. 0x0400 1024 Death of client (DLSw or APPN). 0x0800 2048 Data Path (DP) messages.

wfX25QllcAddrMapGenXid.description: Simulate receiving an XID command from the QLLC device. This object should be enabled when an PU 2.0 QLLC device is connecting thru DLSw to an non-X.25 host.

wfX25QllcAddrMapNodeId.name: wfX25QllcAddrMapNodeId
wfX25QllcAddrMapNodeId.description: The 8 hexadecimal digit Node Identification field of the simulated XID (see wfX25QllcAddrMapGenXid object). This field has two sub-fields, ID Block and ID Number. The first 3 hexadecimal digits are the ID block value and the last 5 hexadecimal digits are the ID Number value.
